		"name": "WooCommerce REST API",
		"description": "# WooCommerce REST API\n\nREST API endpoints for WooCommerce stores.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### 1. Set Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `woo_store_url` | \u2705 | Full store URL (e.g., `https://mystore.com`) |\n| `woo_consumer_key` | \u2705 | REST API consumer key (`ck_...`) |\n| `woo_consumer_secret` | \u2705 | REST API consumer secret (`cs_...`) |\n\n### 2. Generate API Keys\n\n1. Go to WooCommerce \u2192 Settings \u2192 Advanced \u2192 REST API\n2. Click \"Add key\"\n3. Set permissions (Read/Write)\n4. Generate and copy the Consumer Key and Consumer Secret\n\n### 3. Authentication\n\nUses HTTP Basic Authentication with consumer key as username and consumer secret as password.\n\n\n\n## Variables\n\nThis collection includes pre-defined variables. You can set them in two ways:\n\n**Option 1: Collection Variables (Quick Start)**\n1. Click on the collection name\n2. Go to the \"Variables\" tab\n3. Fill in the \"Current value\" column\n\n**Option 2: Environment Variables (Recommended for multiple stores)**\n1. Import `Ecommerce_APIs.postman_environment.json`\n2. Fill in your values\n3. Select the environment in Postman\n\nEnvironment variables override collection variables, so you can use both.\n\n## Endpoints\n\n| Request | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| List Products | Get all products (API v3) |\n| List Products (Legacy) | Get all products (API v2) |\n\n## API Documentation\n\nhttps://woocommerce.github.io/woocommerce-rest-api-docs/\n",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
